- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely because the paper discusses defining transducers in dependent type theory, which is a programming language. 
- cs.TL (Type Theory) is another likely category because the paper deals with representing functions between coinductive types in type theory. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is a possible category because the paper discusses transducers, which are a type of automaton. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category because the paper deals with representing and manipulating data structures (coinductive types) in type theory.
